Install opencv via the terminal
sudo apt-get install libopencv-dev

Install Assimp by cloning from github and building and installing frmo ther
http://assimp.sourceforge.net/main_downloads.html
git clone git://github.com/assimp/assimp.git assimp
cd assimp
make
sudo make install

Install GLEW libraries.

Now to Install ROS, someitmes I was getting package dependency errors in that case, try

sudo aptitude install ros-indigo-desktop-full

When it asks to do the suggestions, press 'y'. When it finished, repeat this task again and again until there are
no more options and it says it changed zero things. It will now be installed.